Definition of personal data
The Electronic Transactions Law defines personal data as any information in relation to a natural person which can be directly or indirectly identified by reference to one or more factors, for example, an identification number.
Definition of sensitive personal data
There is no law defining sensitive personal data. However, the Constitution of the Republic of Mozambique imposes restrictions on recording and handling any individually identifiable information concerning a person’s political, philosophical or ideological beliefs, religious beliefs, membership in a political party or trade union and (particulars) related to the person’s privacy.Last modified 10 Dec 2021
				
			